# ✅ Code Review Checklist Protocol

## Duplicate Prevention
- [ ] No duplicate files with same names exist
- [ ] No duplicate implementations of same functionality
- [ ] No duplicate type definitions
- [ ] No duplicate import statements

## Import Quality
- [ ] All imports use consistent `@/` aliases
- [ ] No relative imports (`../../../`)
- [ ] No unused imports
- [ ] Import order follows convention (React → external → internal)
- [ ] No circular dependencies

## File Organization
- [ ] Components in correct directories (`ui/`, `feature/`)
- [ ] Hooks follow naming convention (`useXxx`)
- [ ] Types in appropriate locations (`types/`, `src/core/types/`)
- [ ] No files in wrong directories
- [ ] File names match content

## Code Quality
- [ ] TypeScript types properly defined
- [ ] No `any` types without justification
- [ ] Error handling implemented
- [ ] Functions have proper JSDoc comments
- [ ] Variables use descriptive names
- [ ] No console.log in production code

## Build & Performance
- [ ] `pnpm build` passes
- [ ] `pnpm lint` passes
- [ ] `pnpm tsc --noEmit` passes
- [ ] No TypeScript errors
- [ ] Bundle size acceptable
- [ ] No performance regressions

## Testing
- [ ] Unit tests written for new functionality
- [ ] Integration tests pass
- [ ] E2E tests updated if needed
- [ ] Test coverage maintained

## Security
- [ ] No sensitive data in code
- [ ] Input validation implemented
- [ ] SQL injection prevention
- [ ] XSS protection in place
- [ ] Authentication/authorization proper

## Documentation
- [ ] Code is self-documenting
- [ ] Complex logic has comments
- [ ] API endpoints documented
- [ ] Breaking changes documented

## Git Standards
- [ ] Commit message follows format
- [ ] No large files committed
- [ ] `.gitignore` respected
- [ ] No merge conflicts
- [ ] Clean git history

## Pre-Merge Checklist
**ALL must pass before merge:**
- [ ] Duplicate detection script passes
- [ ] Import consistency check passes
- [ ] Build verification complete
- [ ] Code review checklist complete
- [ ] Tests pass
- [ ] Documentation updated

## Automated Checks
**CI/CD must verify:**
- Build success
- Test success
- Lint success
- Type check success
- Security scan passes
- Bundle size check passes